revision.text:
A '''spokescouncil''' is a collection of [[affinity groups]] and clusters (a collection of affinity groups), who meet together for a common purpose, often [[civil disobedience]]. "Spokes" is short for "[[spokesperson]]", selected by each affinity group of cluster to represent them in the spokescouncil. The council usually makes decisions via a [[consensus decision making]] process.{{cn|date=November 2011}}

Employment of spokescouncils within the [[United States]] occurred in [[Seattle]], during the [[WTO Ministerial Conference of 1999 protest activity|WTO Ministerial Conference of 1999 protests]] and in [[San Francisco Bay Area]], leading up to "[[March 20, 2003 anti-war protest|Day X]]" - the day-after the U.S. invasion of Iraq in 2003. These took place under the network known as [[Direct Action to Stop the War]] (DASW).{{cn|date=November 2011}}

